          "email": "uja.ornl@yahoo.com",
          "date": "2018-03-30 03:13:44.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-9019 libcfs: discard cfs_time_seconds()",
        "message": "LU-9019 libcfs: discard cfs_time_seconds()\n\ncfs_time_seconds() converts a number of seconds to the\nmatching number of jiffies. The standard way to do this\nin Linux is \"* HZ\". So discard cfs_time_seconds() and\nuse \"* HZ\" instead.\n\nWith lustre now using proper 64 bit time we no longer\nneed the cfs_time_seconds() wrapper. Also using\nmsecs_to_jiffies() no longer works to get around the\nvariable jiffiess issue. With all uses of HZ being\nto the local node it is safe to remove the wrapper.\n\nLinux commit: 672b63e55bdee71150e3cc472f6294e0535a95ad\n\nChange-Id: I1801f930d4789d566eafc01e38af7c026327cb50\nSigned-off-by: NeilBrown <neilb@suse.com>\nSigned-off-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@yahoo.com>\nReviewed-by: James Simmons <jsimmons@infradead.org>\nReviewed-by: Patrick Farrell <paf@cray.com>\nSigned-off-by: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
